review_blob: Bottle from SB, gift from father. Despite what I have been told, not so bad. A rather fresh taste, line a mix of pilsener and ginger ale. Not good, but not too bad.
Bottle from SB. Good taste and aroma, maybe a little thin body but very refreshing. Nice!
Bottle at Jrntorgets brygghus. Not really much aroma. No taste. But at least not a bad taste.
Bottle at restaurant at lunch. A very standard pale lager, with some strange palate. Not too bad, though.
Bottle from SB. An IPA with maybe a little too little taste. It is wasy to drink, but not one of my favourites.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Snow Wit White IPA

review_blob: Bottle from SB. A very rich and balanced IPA, easy to drink but with a lot of flavour. Good!
Bottle from SB. Very rich taste and aroma, still not too bitter. A very good DIPA!
Bottle from SB. Very nice aroma and taste. Very complex taste, kind of a mix between IP, tripel and barley wine. Good!
Bottle at Haket. Pours a lot of head and looks fresh, yellow and inviting. Aroma and taste of orages and citrus. Very good!
Bottle at Haket. A very muddy look, dark and with granules of oak(?). Aroma of strong, malty ale and whisky, at least a hint of oak. Taste is complex and rich. A surprisingly good ale!
Bottle at Haket in Gothenburg. Very nice beer, perfect combination of IPA and red ale. Surprisingly fresh!
Bottle from SB. Fresh aroma with a lot of citrus. Warm body, sweet and different frommany other IPAs. Very easy to drink. Good!
Bottle from SB. I really like Oceanbryggeriet, but I guess I am just not in to cider. Far too little body and aroma for me, I guess I should stick to beer.

Bottle from SB. Aroma with a lot citrus, very fresh. The taste is smooth and balanced. More body than many other session IPAs I have tasted. In all, the best session IPA I have had, a perfect example of a beer with lower abv but still with a lot of taste and body.
Gift from friend. A very good APA, a good balance between body and hops. Nice aroma. A good craft beer!
Bottle from SB. A perfect beer for a warm summer evening, a good balance between light hopiness and dry lager taste. A perfect example of very good pale lager!
Bottle from SB. A very well balanced Imperial Stout, with nice aroma and complex taste. Recommended!
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Oak Aged

review_blob: Bottle from SB. Pours four fingers of head. Aroma with a lot of citrus. Taste is balanced and rather smooth for an IPA. A good one!
beer_name: All In Brewing The Purpose of IPA

review_blob: Bottle at lrepubliken bar and restaurant in Gothenburg. A near-perfect Abbey tripel, well balanced in both taste and aroma. Goes with anything!
Bottle from Coop Varberg. A very watery ale, not much of hops in this despite the name. Not too bad on a warm day, though since the taste is pretty crisp.
Bottle from SB. Very nice taste and aroma, like raisins and chocolate. Easy to drink, but not as powerful taste as imperial porters.
Bottle from SB. Pours one finger of head. Very nice aroma and taste, typically saison. Good!
Bottle from shop in Paraty, Brazil. A very distinct aroma, but rather watery taste.
Bottle from SB. Pours two fingers of head. Aroma with s lot of citrus. Taste is crisp and bitter, very good beer!
Bottle from SB. Very nice taste and aroma, especially considering the relatively low abv. Good!
Bottle from SB. Pours two fingers of head. Nice aroma, but pretty watery taste in my opinion. Totally ok beer, anyway.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Beer Camp Hoppy Lager

review_blob: Bottle at lrepubliken. Very well balanced stout, perfect maltiness and hoppiness. Chocolate and coffee flavours. One of the best beers I have had!
beer_name: Ballast Point Sea Monster Imperial Stout

review_blob: Bottle from SB. A lot of chocolate, roasted barley and cofee in aroma and taste. Very good!

Bottle from trip to Germany. Looks very pale yellow. Aroma is fruity, like cider. So is the taste, sourish, fresh like cider with lively CO2. Almost no aftertaste. A very different beer, but no mango taste.
Bottel from SB. Very malty IPA in my taste, good aroma but not the best I have had. Still very good!
Bottle from SB. Pours a lot of head. It looks pale yellow and not filtered. Nose is typically wheat, like banana. Tastes good!
Bottle from Alko in Tornio. Very nice aroma and taste, a good porter that probably can benefit from ageing.
I had this from tap at a pub in england. As far as I can remember, it was not the best beer I have had.
beer_name: John Smiths Original Bitter / Extra Smooth

review_blob: Bottle from Alko in Torneo. A very nice beer, a golden ale with nice taste and aroma. Recommended!
Bottle from Alko in Torneo. Smells like bread, tastes a lot of alcohol. Still not the worst beer!
Bottle from SB. A very good Porter, a real classic Swedish beer. Nice aroma with hints of chocolate and cofee. Taste is balanced. Pretty easy to drink. Very good!
Bottle from SB. A very special taste and aroma, like burned pancakes with burned sugar. But good!
Bottle at friend. Very nice aroma, taste is also very good but I think I prefer the Brewdog Dogma.
Bottle at friend. Very nice aroma and taste, very good balance and also nice color. Very good!
Can from SB. A pretty ok beer, tastes good bit nothing out of the ordinary.
Can at friend in Kalix. Good to have a second Estonian beer. Tastes good for being a pale lager.
Bottle from SB. A pretty boring amber lager in my opinion. The taste and palate ferls tired and not very tasty. A below-medium beer I guess. Not too bad though.
Bottle from SB. Very nice taste and aroma, plenty of citrus, flowers and fruits. A good beer!
Bottle at restaurant in Sundsvall. Nice amber colour, pours two fingers of head. Taste is good, but nothing exeptional. A good beer!
beer_name: Shepherd Neame Whitstable Bay Organic Ale (Bottle)

review_blob: Bottle from SB. Pours no head. Looks very pale. Smells like old beer cans which are about to be recycled. Tastes almost nothing, a hint of chemicals and metal.
Bottle from SB. Pours three fingers of head. Classic west coast IPA aroma, taste is also very good.
Bottle from SB. Pretty ordinary pale lager, but a hint of taste gives it a surprise. My first Polish beer.
Tap at the Rover in Gothenburg. Color is light yellow and unckeae. Aroma and taste of citrus. Good IPA!
Bottle from Hemkp Kungsbacka. Smells like Pripps bl (bot very nice) and tastes nothing. I prefer water, since it is cheaper!
Bottle from SB. Very nice aroma, a lot of hoppy citrus. Taste is good, bitter but a little to tame. Body is very light, as it is for many session ipas. Pretty ok beer!
